parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain or tensioner can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
shakes
or vibrates while driving
and may not start again. Some complaints mention a loud noise or warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption or leakage can cause engine failure, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Oil spots on the driveway
burning smell from under the car
and sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
shakes
or vibrates while driving
and may not start again. Some complaints mention a warning light on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Carbonization on valves can cause engine misfires, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine misfires
lean fault code
and difficulty driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear main seal failure can cause oil leakage, leading to engine failure and potential accidents.
symptoms: Oil spots on the driveway
burning smell from under the car
and sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fire can cause loss of control and potential accidents, as well as property damage.
symptoms: Intense smoke and fire from the front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control module can cause the fuel pump to run continuously, resulting in a drained battery and/or a no-start condition, or cause a loss of motive power while the vehicle is in motion, which can increase the risk of a crash causing injury and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
the fuel pump module burns up
the fuel pump draws too many amps
the vehicle has a strong fuel odor
and the vehicle has a fuel leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, which can increase the risk of a crash causing injury and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
the fuel pump module burns up
the fuel pump draws too many amps
the vehicle has a strong fuel odor
and the vehicle has a fuel leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in providing a remedy for the recall can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, which can increase the risk of a crash causing injury and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the check engine warning indicator illuminates
the fuel pump module burns up
the fuel pump draws too many amps
the vehicle has a strong fuel odor
and the vehicle has a fuel leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock up, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle shakes while driving
the steering wheel makes a grinding noise
the ABS light and traction light turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the fuel pump error code is displayed
misfires occur
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles while accelerating
the battery drains
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the engine sputters
the check engine light illuminates
the battery light illuminates
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
causing the vehicle to stall or not start
the steering wheel controls stop working
the airbag warning light illuminates
and the display shows "airbag fault".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine fails
causing the vehicle to stall or not start
the engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may not start.
